text: Ali Magrashi (; born 1 October 1999) is a Saudi Arabian footballer who plays as a right back for Saudi Pro League side Al-Shabab . ==Career== Magrashi started his career at Al-Shabab and is a product of the Al-Shabab's youth system. On 30 January 2018, Magrashi made his professional debut for Al-Shabab against Al-Ahli in the Pro League, replacing Abdulwahab Jaafer. On 11 July 2019, Magrashi signed a 5-year professional contract with Al-Shabab. on 30 June 2019, He was chosen in the Saudi program to develop football talents established by General Sports Authority in Saudi Arabia . ==References== ==External links== * Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Saudi Arabian footballers Category:Saudi Arabia youth international footballers Category:Association football fullbacks Category:Saudi Professional League players Category:Al-Shabab FC (Riyadh) players
